[h3 id=AboutTheGame 
	" About the Game
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	[em 
		"The Golden Baton
	]em
	" is a 1983 text adventure released by Digital Fantasia, and is the 1st installment in Brian Howarth's 
	[em 
		"Mysterious Adventures
	]em
	" series. Your mission is to recover the Golden Baton, a priceless artefact that holds within it a kind of life force that maintains the equilibrium between good and evil. Stolen from the Palace of King Ferrenuil, the kingdom is already beginning to feel the effects of drought and pestilence.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=AboutTheTas 
	" About the TAS
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"This TAS aims to complete the game as fast as possible.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=Gameplay 
	" Gameplay
	$LF
]h3
[h4 id=TapeLoading 
	" Tape Loading
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"The first ~44% of this TAS is simply loading the tape. Loading finishes on frame 11174 (~4:40).
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=TypingPatterns 
	" Typing Patterns
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"The usual optimal typing pattern looks like this:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"T
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Y
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"P
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"I
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"N
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"G
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"But a few times, this pattern can be disrupted by typing the 2nd letter of a command 2-3 frames after the first during text loading. Then the pattern looks like this:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"T
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Y
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"P
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"I
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"N
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"G
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"It's possible to input the 1st letter of a command while a picture is loading. Depending on whether the game lags from this or not, this can save 1 frame every time it's done.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Also, we can only press one key 10 times a second, meaning that when we have to type 2 of the same letter in a row, there's a 5 frame delay.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=WordShortening 
	" Word Shortening
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Words that are 5 letters or longer don't have to be typed out in full, and can instead be shortened to 4 letters, for example:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" QUARTZ = QUAR
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" MATCHES = MATC
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" PADLOCK = PADL
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"You get the idea.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Gameplay continues like this while waiting through cutscenes until input ends on frame 25631, when we enter the command "GET BATO" (GET BATON).
	$LF
]div
